The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, gave remarks at the funeral of Ravi Zacharias, a renowned Christian apologist. Pence expressed his condolences to the Zacharias family and praised Ravi for his intellectual contributions to Christianity. He emphasized Ravi's ability to engage skeptics with kindness and respect, while sharing the message of hope and love. Pence also acknowledged the timing of Ravi's passing amidst the coronavirus pandemic, expressing gratitude for his comforting voice during these difficult times. He likened Ravi to a "gentle giant of the faith" and highlighted his impact on countless lives around the world. Pence concluded by expressing his belief in the eternal life of Ravi and offering prayers for his family and all those grieving during these unprecedented times.